## 🧱 Week 1 — HTML Structure of Your Portfolio

### First, understand how HTML works

HTML is like the **skeleton** of a webpage. It gives structure. Think of it like building a house — HTML is the walls and rooms. CSS is the paint and decoration. JavaScript is the electricity (makes things work).

Every HTML element looks like this:
```html
<tagname> content goes here </tagname>
```
The first one is the **opening tag**, the second with `/` is the **closing tag**.

---

### The 3 rules of HTML structure

**Rule 1** — Every HTML file starts with this exact skeleton:
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <!-- Info about the page — not visible to user -->
</head>
<body>
    <!-- Everything visible to user goes here -->
</body>
</html>
```

**Rule 2** — `<head>` holds page settings. `<body>` holds everything you see.

**Rule 3** — Tags are **nested** — one inside another, like boxes inside boxes.

